WGC HSBC CHAMPIONS
October 31, 2019
Im Sungjae
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
 Q.  Can you talk about your round, 6-under 66, what worked for you?  
IM SUNGJAE: My tee shot was pretty good. Iron shot, the distance control was really well. The trajection was pretty good, too. Also, the putting was pretty well.   
 Q.  Your first time in the WGC-HSBC Champions, your first time to this golf course. How do you find the golf course, is it something that suits your game, suits your style?  
IM SUNGJAE: The grass, I like it. My iron shots, pretty well to play with this grass.   
 Q.  Last week in Japan, you won on the Korean Tour. What are you happy with in your game right now? Do you feel like you're very comfortable and you're playing your best golf right now or can you still play better?  
IM SUNGJAE: My condition daily basis is consistent, every day is not that bad, not that great, but it's consistent. That's why I played good.   
 Q.  Do you feel like a win is just around the corner for you, and what do you think you need to do to try and get that?  
IM SUNGJAE: Right now, the feeling is consistency, it's pretty good to be Top-10 or topside. If my putting is helping me out, and also my luck come to me, maybe I can win.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT